:<div>

shoe /ʃuː/

(shoeing,shod,shoes) 

1. N-COUNT Shoes are objects which you wear on your feet. They cover most of your foot and you wear them over socks or stockings. 鞋 

例： ...a pair of shoes. …一双鞋。 

例： Low-heeled comfortable shoes are best. 舒适的低跟鞋是最好的。 

2. N-COUNT A shoe is the same as a . 马蹄铁 

3. V-T When a blacksmith shoes a horse, they attach horseshoes onto their feet. 给…钉蹄铁 

例： Blacksmiths spent most of their time repairing tools and shoeing horses. 铁匠们把他们大部分时间用来修理工具和给马钉蹄铁。 

4. PHRASE If you fill someone's shoes or step into their shoes , you take their place by doing the job they were doing. 接替某人的位置 

例： No one has been able to fill his shoes. 没有人能接替他的工作。 

5. PHRASE If you talk about being in someone's shoes , you talk about what you would do or how you would feel if you were in their situation. 处在某人的境地 

例： I wouldn't want to be in his shoes. 我不愿意处于他的境地。

</div>

